<!doctype html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1"><title>Manual QA Testing Finland | Luxival</title><meta name="description" content="Manual and exploratory QA testing for websites and software releases in Finland."><link rel="canonical" href="https://www.luxival.com/qa-audits/manual-qa/"><link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/silo-hubs.css?v=20260718-3"></head><body><header class="hub-header"><a class="hub-brand" href="/">LUXIVAL</a><nav><a href="/qa-audits/">QA &amp; Audits</a><a href="/contact">Contact</a></nav></header><main><section class="hub-hero hub-shell"><p class="hub-kicker">Exploratory · Functional · Regression</p><h1>Manual and exploratory QA testing</h1><p class="hub-lead">Human-led testing for workflows, edge cases, usability problems, error recovery, responsive behaviour, and release risk.</p></section><section class="hub-shell hub-section qa-copy"><h2>Evidence your team can act on</h2><p>Manual QA is appropriate where user judgement, incomplete requirements, rapid change, or unusual combinations make scripted checks insufficient. Sessions can focus on a feature, release candidate, browser matrix, customer journey, or known risk area.</p><p>Findings include environment, severity, reproduction steps, expected result, actual result, and visual evidence where useful. A concise release summary distinguishes blocking defects from lower-risk improvements.</p><a class="hub-button" href="/qa-audits/#request-quote">Request manual QA</a></section></main></body></html>
